l of everything that the band is about. It&#39;s got the nostalgia in there and the history in there, but it&#39;s also got the fun and reverence and childhood charm. And it&#39;s got the rebellion, but it&#39;s got the technology too,” he continued.</p><p> “So it&#39;s this really cool rebirth of everything – or the best of everything that we&#39;ve done, but done the way people always wished we would have done it! [They&#39;re] like, &#39;Right, you guys aren&#39;t half bad now!&#39;你知道？ &#39;Thank you!&#39;” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="与汤姆·德隆格对话|艺术家签名系列|挡泥板" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/DtHFpFSiYxc?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Although the guitarist didn&#39;t provide any further information on the upcoming Blink album, he did, however, explain how the design of his new signature axe is in keeping with his current songwriting style.</p><p> “I try to write music that is accessible and easy to play and enjoy, so that people can come along for the ride,” he explained in the video, sharing his inspiration behind the design.</p><p> “This simplicity really inspired this new signature Stratocaster. It just has one knob and one pickup, which just makes it easy to turn it up, play and sound great, especially important when you&#39;re in front of a crowd and already have plenty to think about.</p><p> “On top of that, the bright colours give it a timeless, California feel that stands out on any stage. Together with Fender, a brand that is deeply rooted in my musical identity, we&#39;ve created something that really stands the test of time – like I strive to do with my music.”</p><p> The Limited Edition Tom DeLonge Stratocaster is available now on Fender for £1,299 and comes with the choice of four colourways. Find out more <a href="https://www.fender.com/en-GB/limited-edition-tom-delonge-stratocaster/0148020306.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> . </p><figure id="attachment_3473796" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3473796" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3473796" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Tom-Delonge-Fender-2023-stratocaster@2000x1270.jpeg" alt="Tom DeLonge with his new Limited Edition Fender Stratocaster." width="2000" height="2500" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Tom-Delonge-Fender-2023-stratocaster@2000x1270.jpeg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Tom-Delonge-Fender-2023-stratocaster@2000x1270-400x500.jpeg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Tom-Delonge-Fender-2023-stratocaster@2000x1270-800x1000.jpeg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Tom-Delonge-Fender-2023-stratocaster@2000x1270-696x870.jpeg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Tom-Delonge-Fender-2023-stratocaster@2000x1270-1392x1740.jpeg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Tom-Delonge-Fender-2023-stratocaster@2000x1270-1068x1335.jpeg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3473796" class="wp-caption-text"> Tom DeLonge with his new Limited Edition Fender Stratocaster. CREDIT: Fender</figcaption></figure><p> This isn&#39;t the first time that the members have teased their upcoming album in 2023. Earlier this year, drummer <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/travis-barker-gives-promising-update-on-new-blink-182-album-3437436">Travis Barker told fans the project be finished before they head out on tour next year</a> and, in January, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/tom-delonge-teases-new-blink-182-album-is-the-best-weve-ever-made-3373665">DeLonge took to Instagram to write that the upcoming LP is “the best album we&#39;ve ever made.”</a></p><p> “Buckle up. I&#39;m personally tripping and so proud of what we have created TOGETHER,” he wrote, sharing a picture of the cartoon rabbit from the poster of the band&#39;s 1999 &#39;Loserkids&#39; tour. “As one unified force of fun, eternal youth, and most of all – close friends.”</p><p> Additionally, the band have so far released one single – &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/blink-182-welcome-tom-delonge-back-with-anthemic-new-single-edging-3328729">Edging</a> &#39; – while DeLonge also promised that the record contains some of their “ <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/tom-delonge-says-new-blink-182-album-is-their-most-progressive-3329318">most progressive</a> ” music so far.</p><p> The forthcoming LP will be the first full-length release from the classic line-up – DeLonge, Barker and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mark-hoppus">Mark Hoppus</a> – since <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/blink-182-reunite-with-tom-delonge-announce-new-music-and-world-tour-buy-tickets-3326660">their reunion last year.</a></p><p> Having wrapped up the North American leg of the tour earlier this month, Blink-182 are set to kick off their <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/blink-182-reunite-with-tom-delonge-announce-new-music-and-world-tour-buy-tickets-3326660">UK run of live shows later this year</a> . This will start in Glasgow, with two back-to-back performances at the OVO Hydro arena on September 1 and 2, before making stops in cities including London, Birmingham and Manchester.</p><p> Find a full list of upcoming tour dates below, and find remaining tickets <a href="https://ticketmaster-uk.tm7559.net/c/2862475/431519/7559?sharedid=NME&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ticketmaster.co.uk%2Fblink182-tickets%2Fartist%2F945149" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> .</p><h2> <strong>Blink-182&#39;s UK and Ireland tour dates are:</strong></h2><p><strong>九月</strong><br /><strong>1 – Glasgow, OVO Hydro</strong><br /> <strong>2 – Glasgow, OVO Hydro</strong><br /> <strong>4 – Belfast, SSE Arena</strong><br /> <strong>5 – Dublin, 3Arena</strong></p><p><strong>十月</strong><br /><strong>11 – London, The O2</strong><br /> <strong>12 – London, The O2</strong><br /> <strong>14 – Birmingham, Utilita Arena</strong><br /> <strong>15 – Manchester, AO Arena</strong><br /> <strong>16 – Manchester, AO Arena</strong></p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/tom-delonge-blink-182-new-album-probably-our-best-3473791">Blink-182&#39;s Tom DeLonge: “I think our album coming out is probably our best album we&#39;ve ever made”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 The Strokes 的 Julian Casablancas 分享了他对 1975 年马来西亚 LGBTQ 争议的看法https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-中风-julian-casablancas-shares-his-thoughts-on-the-1975s-malaysia-lgbtq-controversy-3473769?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=the-笔画朱利安卡萨布兰卡斯分享他对 1975 年代马来西亚 LGBTQ 争议的看法Hollie GeraghtyWed, 26 Jul 2023 14:13:16 +0000 Music NewsNewsIndieRock https://www.nme.com/?p=3473769 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>主唱承认“还有很多事情需要解决”，但在涉及其他文化时“我们应该有策略”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-strokes-julian-casablancas-shares-his-thoughts-on-the-1975s-malaysia-lgbtq-controversy-3473769">The Strokes 的 Julian Casablancas 分享了他对 1975 年马来西亚 LGBTQ 争议的看法，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-strokes">The Strokes</a>的朱利安·<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/julian-casablancas">卡萨布兰卡斯 (Julian Casablancas)</a>分享了他对<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-1975">The 1975</a>最近在马来西亚引发的争议的看法，该争议导致他们因在舞台上对 LGBTQ 问题采取立场而被禁赛。</p><p>上周末， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-good-vibes-festival-malaysia-set-cut-short-matty-healy-criticises-anti-lgbtq-laws-kiss-bassist-3471738">The 1975 在吉隆坡 Good Vibes 音乐节上的演出被缩短</a>，随后音乐节的其余部分也被取消，原因是主唱<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/matty-healy">马蒂·希利 (Matty Healy)</a>批评反 LGBTQ 法律并在台上亲吻了贝斯手罗斯·麦克唐纳 (Ross MacDonald)。</p><p>在周五（7 月 21 日）的头条表演中，希利向马来西亚政府表示：“我不认为邀请 1975 来到一个国家，然后告诉我们可以与谁发生性关系有什么意义。”</p><p>此后， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-banned-from-malaysia-good-vibes-festival-cancelled-matty-healy-3471893">The 1975 被禁止在该国演出</a>， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/malaysian-lgbtq-community-condemn-the-1975s-matty-healy-over-kiss-incident-3472125">主唱也遭到了马来西亚 LGBTQ+ 群体的强烈反对</a>，声称他的行为破坏了当地活动人士多年来的行动。</p><p> 1975 现在还可能<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-malaysia-good-vibes-festival-cancelled-class-action-lawsuit-artists-vendors-3473217">面临马来西亚艺术家和节日供应商因节日取消而提起的集体诉讼</a>。 </p><figure id="attachment_3473221" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3473221" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3473221" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images.jpg" alt="《1975》的马蒂·希利和罗斯·麦克唐纳" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3473221" class="wp-caption-text"> The 1975 乐队的 Matty Healy 和 Ross Macdonald 在 2023 年 Parklife 音乐节上表演。图片来源：Shirlaine Forrest/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> The Strokes 的卡萨布兰卡斯无法与乐队一起在 Good Vibes Festival 上演出，他<a href="https://www.nme.com/en_asia/news/music/the-strokes-good-vibes-festival-cancelled-replacement-show-malaysia-kuala-lumpur-julian-casablancas-3472345">本周末在社交媒体上分享说，他们目前正在研究在马来西亚演出的方法</a>。</p><p>这位主唱随后在<a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CvBQHpAJD5C/?igshid=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram 的</a>回复中详细阐述了他对这场争议的看法，写道：“这确实帮助了白人局外人的意识，是的，当然……我也有同样的感觉。不知道。但当你仔细研究它时，你会发现马来西亚的情况可能几乎不会改变。这就像说你帮助人们认识到韩国的不公正现象……在那些推特压力不会起作用的情况下，他们不在乎，那里的政府很严厉。”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="es" dir="ltr">洛杉矶球迷马蒂·希利 (Matty Healy) 与朱利安 (Julian) 独奏。 <a href="https://t.co/iWp1n8Yw2U">pic.twitter.com/iWp1n8Yw2U</a></p><p> — 费尔南达·托雷斯 (@MaferGooner) <a href="https://twitter.com/MaferGooner/status/1682983403266646017?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 7 月 23 日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>在另一条评论中，卡萨布兰卡斯更深入地阐述了他的想法，承认他认为希利的意思是“一件积极的事情”，最初同意“提高认识是件好事”。但他表示，一个人应该“对自己不熟悉的文化保持了解和尊重”。</p><p>他接着说：“有很多事情需要解决，但我们应该采取战略性的措施……没有对此事发表评论——只是一个局外人[原文如此]认为这会对马来西亚产生任何影响……它似乎会产生更多的负面后果……你的傻瓜[原文如此]允许在那里直接公开亲吻，我相信……这是一个不同的世界，不是他的工作来修复然后保释……如果他留下来并入狱，那么该死的，尊重。但我认为他只是开了个玩笑/笑了[原文如此]，然后坐头等舱飞回家，我猜。”</p><p>这位音乐家继续澄清他的想法，分享“断章取义”并暗示“朱利安对某某感到愤怒”是“互联网上普遍无知的一个典型例子”。</p><p>卡萨布兰卡斯在另一条评论中表示，他认为“为他辩护是英雄有点白人”。</p><p> 1975 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-cancel-indonesia-taiwan-banned-malaysia-3471980">在被马来西亚禁止后也取消了在印度尼西亚和台湾的演出</a>，而截至周二（7 月 25 日），已就该事件向<a href="https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2023/07/25/the-1975-left-country-even-before-report-lodged-against-them-says-deputy-igp#cxrecs_s" target="_blank" rel="noopener">警方提交了 18 份报告</a>。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-strokes-julian-casablancas-shares-his-thoughts-on-the-1975s-malaysia-lgbtq-controversy-3473769">The Strokes 的 Julian Casablancas 分享了他对 1975 年马来西亚 LGBTQ 争议的看法，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
